{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3fb46454-4a08-4239-86dc-c95fa17fffe4","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 3.x → 4.x dropped the VSTest bridge by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **4.0.0**, the SDK uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new `dotnet test` integration) exclusively. The VSTest compatibility layer (`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge`) is **no longer included**, so `vstest.console.exe` can't discover or run tests.\n\n### Your options\n\n1. **Switch your CI to the new runner** (recommended):\n   ```\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n   With MSTest.Sdk 4.x this uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively — no VSTest needed.\n\n2. **Re-enable the VSTest bridge** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n   This restores compatibility with `vstest.console`.\n\nOption 1 is the intended migration path; option 2 is a stopgap if you can't change your CI tooling yet.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cbea842f-21e8-41d5-8934-4e8df686e2a5","outputTokens":287,"requestId":"3408:10D6CE:120E70:15E259:69F416E1"},"id":"56e0a28f-3527-4668-8c11-578f6bf850c4","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:58:48.898Z","parentId":"3ae27858-363d-45f8-85ff-9f95ca57647a"}
